[1]
Date: 11 Sep 2012
From: Amanda Walsh [edited]
<Amanda.Walsh@hpa.org.uk>


In response to ProMED posting "ANTHRAX, HUMAN - UNITED KINGDOM (07): (ENGLAND) FATAL", for clarification we can confirm that the wording used in the HPA press statement is a standard phrase and doesn't mean there was any uncertainty about the information given.

We can also confirm that the case in Wales is separate and this was confirmed by Public Health Wales on Fri 7 Sep 2012.
http://www.wales.nhs.uk/sitesplus/888/news/24028.

--
Mandy Walsh
Emerging Infections and Zoonoses
Health Protection Agency: Health Protection Services, Colindale
London, England.
<Amanda.Walsh@hpa.org.uk>

