My understanding is that this is the 2nd addict from Blackpool to have died of anthrax. The Welsh patient is still alive as far as I know.

--
Robert Spencer,
(presently on sabbatical leave)
<Bob.Spencer@hpa.org.uk>

[Pose a question and folk present the answer. In a severely economically challenged city with casinos and unemployment it is to be expected that there are drug addicts who it seems, unfortunately, are unaware of the need to seek medical help as soon as one develops a fever and without any delays. In the "old days" Blackpool was a much favoured place for working folk in the Midlands to go to for fun with music halls, restaurants & bars, dance halls, lots of celebrities, nationally known illuminations, beach front. Those days are long past.

One more news report but it adds little:
http://www.metro.co.uk/news/911444-outbreak-fears-as-second-heroin-user-dies-from-anthrax-infection

And thanks to Mandy and Bob for satisfying the academic curiosity of this questioning moderator. - Mod.MHJ

